.TH JENNIFER 1 "2026" "Jennifer" "Jennifer Programming Language"
.SH NAME
jennifer \- Jennifer programming language interpreter (TinyGo build)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jennifer
.I subcommand
.RI [ args ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jennifer
is the canonical TinyGo build of the Jennifer interpreter.
It is the small, embeddable variant of the language; the standard-Go
build is shipped alongside as
.BR jennifer-go (1)
for users running compute-bound Jennifer where the performance gap
matters more than binary size.
.PP
Jennifer is a small, experimental, interpreted programming language.
Source files use the
.B .j
extension. The language reference and library documentation ship in
.IR /usr/share/doc/jennifer/ .
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.BR run " " \fIfile.j\fR
Execute a Jennifer source file. Pass
.B -
as the filename to read from standard input.
.TP
.BR repl
Start the interactive read-eval-print loop. Built-in line editor
with cursor keys, history, and standard editing shortcuts when stdin
is a terminal.
.TP
.BR tokens " " \fIfile.j\fR
Print the lexer's token stream for the given source file.
.TP
.BR ast " " \fIfile.j\fR
Print the parsed abstract syntax tree as JSON.
.TP
.BR fmt " " \fIfile.j\fR
Format the source file per the project style guide and print to
standard output. (No in-place rewrite.)
.TP
.BR version
Print the build version.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/mime/packages/jennifer.xml
Shared MIME information that registers the
.B .j
extension as
.BR text/x-jennifer .
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR jennifer-go (1),
.UR https://github.com/mplx/jennifer-lang
.UE
